Introduction

Chocolate was a five-member girl group under H-Line Entertainment. They debuted on August 27, 2010, with the digital single "What To Do." In October 2010, the group faced some controversy after their CEO was involved in a sexual bribery scandal. The following month, Cheryl confirmed that the members had decided to go their separate ways, and the group was believed to have disbanded.
